metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #247
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.name: Missingno #275
metadata.description:
Containment has been breached and Missingno is on the loose. 
This unique beast doesn’t have a fixed shape and its appearance is ever-changing. 
Some call it a bug, very few know what it is truly made of.

Only now with present technology we managed to capture a fraction of its unlimited possible faces. 

Mint for a unique picture of Missingno, yet outdated the very moment it’s taken.


(Open live and click on the image to export)

metadata.name: Glomularus #44
metadata.description:
Glomularus is an exploration in generative, artificial life forms. The project is an extension of my Protobyte series, begun in 2004.

Driven by Verlet icosahedra and responsive tendrils, Glomulari live in a spherical virtual ecosystem (V-eco) enhanced through user interaction.

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
  drag -> camera rotation
  drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
  scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
  1-9: add acceleration
  -, +: reduce | increase V-eco sphere radius
  f, g: reduce | increase fog
  p: screen capture

Tip:
To decrease creature acceleration, reduce V-eco sphere radius

Note:
Please post your favorite Glomularus screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: Summer City #23
metadata.description:
The summer city-scapes bring you back to when you were a kid and used to draw your dreams with coloured chalks on a blackboard or on playground at school. Just waiting for vacation to come and to enjoy the freedom near the sea.
It was my specific choice to generate filling by using lines like I would have done with a chalk in my hands. 
The collection has many variations both in contents and in form factor / mode / palettes.
Gold mode is rare.
Hit the 's' key to save the file

metadata.name: Lucky Oracles #232
metadata.description:
"Lucky Oracles" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022

Eko33, is a Swiss-French generative artist who has been at the forefront of digital arts since 1999 when he started writing code to create generative artworks and installations. He made his debut using a Commodore SX-64 and floppy disks. Since then, his work has been exhibited in Museums, International art fairs, and biennales. His work is focused on nonfigurative, generative art while using custom algorithms and innovative technology.

Official Website: https://www.eko33.com/ Official Twitter account: https://twitter.com/eko3316 Official Instagram account: https://www.instagram.com/eko33studio/ https://linktr.ee/eko33 "I create deterministic generative art based on crypto hash seeds. Maximizing algorithmic diversity."

If you want to receive an e-mail alert when I release new artwork subscribe here => https://eko33.com/email-alerts

metadata.name: Unicorn #3361
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.
